It’s understood the toddler was sexually assaulted allegedly by the man known to her. JOHANNESBURG - The parents of a two-year-old girl who was raped in Reiger Park, east of Joburg, are calling for justice to be served. It’s understood the toddler was sexually assaulted allegedly by the man known to her. The 34-year-old has been arrested and is expected to appear in the Boksburg Magistrates Court on Monday on charges of rape. The child's father said he was worried about his daughter: “Me being a father that works so far away, I fear for my child.”